text: The Manly Warringah Sea Eagles is an Australian professional rugby league team. The team is based on the Northern Beaches of Sydney, New South Wales. They were founded in 1946. They currently play in the National Rugby League competition. They have won eight premierships, most recently in 2011. Manly Sea Eagles have won 8 Grand Finals: * 1972 * 1973 * 1976 * 1978 * 1987 * 1996 * 2008, * 2011 Their home ground is Brookvale Oval, which is affectionately known by locals as "Fortress Brookie". ==Other websites== * *Northern Beaches Council - Brookvale Oval Category:National Rugby League Category:Sports clubs and teams in Sydney Category:1946 establishments in Australia
